                    <abstract lang="eng">This article presents the conception of a tool chain system that is capable of performing various operations on data sets from multimodal interaction research. We argue that such a tool chain can improve the workflow of scientists by providing a flexible way of performing recurring tasks from the area of creating, postprocessing, and analysing multimodal data collections.</abstract>
